<javascript-typescript-indentation>

<title>JavaScript/TypeScript Indentation Standards</title>

<context>
<applies-to>All JavaScript and TypeScript files (.js, .jsx, .ts, .tsx)</applies-to>
</context>

<rules>
- Always use 2 spaces for indentation
- Never use tabs for indentation
- Configure editor to show spaces when tab key is pressed
- Maintain consistent indentation throughout the file
- Each nested block increases indentation by 2 spaces
- Align multi-line statements with the opening delimiter
</rules>

<examples>
<example type="good">
```typescript
function processData(items: string[]) {
  const results = items.map((item) => {
    if (item.length > 0) {
      return item.toUpperCase();
    }
    return '';
  });
  
  return results.filter((result) => 
    result !== '' &&
    result.length < 10
  );
}
```
</example>

<example type="bad">
```typescript
